headline: 2 Healthcare Stocks with Promising Prospects and 1 to Think Twice About
summary: Personal health and wellness is one of the many secular tailwinds for healthcare companies. But financial performance has lagged recently as players offloaded surplus COVID inventories in 2023 and 2024, a headwind for overall demand. The result? Over the past six months, the industry has tumbled by 13%. This performance was worse than the S&P 500’s 5.5% fall.
